Bank Management System (C)
Project Overview

Bank Management System is a simple menu-driven project developed in C language. The project simulates basic banking operations and stores account information permanently using file handling.
This project was created to practice core C programming concepts such as structures, functions, switch case, and file operations.

->Features
.Create New Bank Account
.Deposit Money
.Withdraw Money
.Balance Enquiry
.Search Account by Account Number
.PIN Verification for Security
.Store Account Details using File Handling
.Exit System

->Concepts Used
.C Programming
.Structures (struct)
.Functions
.File Handling (fopen, fread, fwrite)
.Conditional Statements
.Switch Case
.Menu Driven Programming
.Project Structure
.bank_management

->How It Works
1.User creates a bank account.
2.Account details are saved in bank.txt.
3.User can deposit and withdraw money.
4.PIN is required before accessing account details.
5.Balance enquiry shows current balance.
6.Search feature finds account using account number.
7.File Storage

The project uses:

bank.txt

This file stores:

-Account Number
-Customer Name
-PIN
-Account Balance

Data remains available after closing the program.

